<TITLE> Recession taskforce members named </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 18 (bdnews24.com)The government Wednesday named the members of the newly constituted 27-member taskforce on confronting the global recession. "Finance minister Abul Maal Abdul Muhith has been made the convenor," said a finance division circular. The task force includes four ministers, an adviser, eminent economists, top business leaders and a representative each from the main political parties Awami League, BNP and Jatiya Party, said the circular. Agriculture Minister Motia Chowdhury, textile minister Abdul Latif Siddiqi, expatriates welfare minister Mosharraf Hossain, commerce minister Faruq Khan and finance, planning adviser Moshiur Rahman and Bangladesh Bank governor Saleh Uddin Ahmed have been named. Former finance minister M Saiduzzaman, economists Rehman Sobhan, Wahiduddin Mahmud, Kazi Kholiquzzaman and Prof Abul Barakat, BIDS director general Kazi Shahabuddin and Centre for Policy Dialogue's executive director Mostafizur Rahman are among the experts. Finance secretary Muhammad Tarek, commerce secretary Firoz Ahmed, IRD secretary and NBR chairman M Abdul Majid, ERD secretary Mosharraf Hossain Bhuiyan are among the top bureaucrats in the new body. FBCCI president Annisul Huq, MCCI president Hafiz Uddin, BGMEA chief Abdus Salam Murshedi, BKMEA boss Fazul Haque, Asian Tiger Capital's Ifti Islam and Samunnay chairman Atiur Rahman represent businesses and civil society. Representatives of the main political parties are yet to be named since the ministry is awaiting responses from the three main parties, the circular added. The main tasks are to identify the channels through which the recession will impact Bangladesh, make quarterly analysis and evaluation of the impacts, boost investments pursue beneficial policies, reduce unnecessary government spending, energise agriculture sectors and stay cautious about important fiscal policies, among others. About its objectives the finance minister told bdnews24.com, "We expect a positive results." bdn
